<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1925-08-18T06:24:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1925-08-18T06:24:00-05:00" n="310" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d310">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">611.60 p 31/21: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Latvia</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">White</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Riga</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1925-08-18T13:00:00+01:36"><hi rend="italic">August 18,
                                        1925—1 p.m.</hi></date><lb/>[Received August 18—10:50
                                a.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>74. In view of my telegram number 73, August 12, 4 p.m., does
                            Department’s telegraphic instruction number 41, August 11, 3 p.m., still
                            stand?</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">White</hi></signed></closer>
